I'll tackle the problem of proving that the intersection of two binomial random graphs is also binomial, specifically that if $G_1 \sim G(V, p)$ and $G_2 \sim G(V, q)$ are independent, then $G_1 \cap G_2 \sim G(V, p \cdot q)$.

